The number of coronavirus cases in South Africa country has risen to 579 140 after 6 275 new cases were confirmed in the past 24 hours. The Department of Health says 286 more people have died from COVID-19 related deaths, bringing the total death toll in the country to 11 556. As of Friday, the total number of recoveries is 461 734, translating to a total recovery rate of 79%. “42 deaths from the Eastern Cape, 20 from the Free State, 26 from the North West,  76 from Gauteng, 54 from KwaZulu-Natal, 22 from Mpumalanga, 18 from the Northern Cape and 28 from the Western Cape,” reads a statement from Health department. The Western Cape still has the highest number of fatalities in the country with 3 534 followed by Gauteng and Eastern Cape with 2 867 and 2 442 respectively. 3 378 029 583 653 466 941 105 035 11 677 478 618 As at  15 August 2020 26 918 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document));